為了避免可能的破壞，帝王谷內的大部分墓穴並不對外開放，而總共18個開放的墓穴亦很少在同一時間開放，關閉墓穴通常是為了進行修復工作<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thebanmappingproject.com/about/KVMasterplan/KVM_CH5.pdf|publisher=Theban Mapping Project|title=KV Condition Surveys|accessdate=2008-08-09|format=PDF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003075946/http://www.thebanmappingproject.com/about/KVMasterplan/KVM_CH5.pdf|archive-date=2008-10-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。參觀KV62的遊客為帝王谷帶來額外的收入。帝王谷西谷僅有[[第十八王朝|第十八王朝]]法老阿伊的陵墓開放，遊客亦需另行購票方可進入參觀<ref>{{cite web|title=Visitor Management in KV|publisher=Theban Mapping Project|url=http://www.thebanmappingproject.com/about/KVMasterplan/KVM_CH7.pdf|accessdate=2008-08-09|format=PDF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003075938/http://www.thebanmappingproject.com/about/KVMasterplan/KVM_CH7.pdf|archive-date=2008-10-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。現在導遊不再能在墓穴內為遊客講解，而遊客在參觀時亦要保持安靜，參觀時亦要以單程的路線團體進出，目的是為了減少參觀的時間及降低遊客對墓穴壁畫的損壞，另外，嚴禁在墓內拍照<ref>Ambros (2001), p.181</ref>。

帝王谷每天平均能吸引4000至5000旅客，而當內河船可在尼羅河行駛的時候，遊客的數量可升至9000人左右，預期到了2015年更會升至25000人<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.kv5.com/articles/article_2.5.html | title=The Valley Today | publisher=Theban Mapping Project | accessdate=2006-12-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061031200107/http://www.kv5.com/articles/article_2.5.html | archive-date=2006-10-31 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

